{"word":"Joshua","slug":"joshua","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Joshua</b> <a href=\"#/H3091\">H3091</a> <br/> 1. Called also Jehoshua, and Jehoshuah, and Oshea:<br/> - Son of Nun<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=13&verse=8'>Num 13:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=7&verse=27'>1Ch 7:27</a> <br/> - Intimately associated with Moses<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=2&chapter=24&verse=13'>Exo 24:13</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=2&chapter=32&verse=17'>Exo 32:17</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=2&chapter=33&verse=11'>Exo 33:11</a> <br/> - A religious zealot<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=11&verse=28'>Num 11:28</a> <br/> - Sent with others to view the promised land<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=13&verse=8'>Num 13:8</a> <br/> - Makes favorable report<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=14&verse=10'>Num 14:10</a> <br/> - Rewarded for his courage and fidelity<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=14&verse=30'>Num 14:30</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=14&verse=38'>Num 14:38</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=32&verse=12'>Num 32:12</a> <br/> - Commissioned, ordained, and charged with the responsibilities of Moses' office<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=27&verse=23'>Num 27:23</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=1&verse=38'>Deu 1:38</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=3&verse=28'>Deu 3:28</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=31&verse=3'>Deu 31:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=31&verse=7'>Deu 31:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=31&verse=23'>Deu 31:23</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=34&verse=9'>Deu 34:9</a> <br/> - Divinely inspired<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=27&verse=18'>Num 27:18</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=34&verse=9'>Deu 34:9</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=1&verse=5'>Jos 1:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=1&verse=9'>Jos 1:9</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=3&verse=7'>Jos 3:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=8&verse=8'>Jos 8:8</a> <br/> - His life miraculously preserved when he made a favorable report of the land<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=14&verse=10'>Num 14:10</a> <br/> - Promises to<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=1&verse=9'>Jos 1:9</a> <br/> - Leads the people into the land of Canaan<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=1'>Joh 1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=7&verse=45'>Act 7:45</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=58&chapter=4&verse=8'>Heb 4:8</a> <br/> - Renews circumcision of the children of Israel; reestablishes the Passover; has a vision of the angel of God<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=5&verse=15'>Jos 5:15</a> <br/> - Besieges and takes Jericho<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=6'>Jos 6</a> <br/> - Takes Ai<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=7'>Joh 7</a> <br/> - Makes a league with the Gibeonites<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=9&verse=27'>Jos 9:27</a> <br/> - The kings of the six nations of the Canaanites:<br/> b Confederate against him<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=9&verse=2'>Jos 9:2</a><br/> b Make war upon the Gibeonites; are defeated and slain<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=10'>Jos 10</a><br/> - Defeats seven other